<!---------------------------->
<table cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Recommended Level<br>for starting quest:</b></td><td valign="bottom"> 35<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting zone:</b></td><td valign="top"> Eastern Wastes<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Additional zones:</b></td><td valign="top"> -<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting NPC:</b></td><td valign="top"> Garadain Glacierbane<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Reward:</b></td><td valign="top"> First Coldain Ring (Copper)<br><br></td></tr>
</table>

First of all, you must be on Coldain faction and probably plan on staying on it for awhile.  This is the beginning of a series of quests of which there are ten parts.<Br>
<br>
Find Garadain Glacierbane in the Coldain Camp just north of the Ry'Gorr fort.  The Loc is approximately -2600, -400.  When you talk to him, he will ask you to help prove yourself to the cause by making a blanket for him.  To make the blanket you must find 2 High Quality Cougar Skins (non stackable) and 2 High Quality Tundra Kodiak Pelts (stackable) and combine them in a Sewing Kit.  The trivial for this has been reported to be anywhere from 41-80.  I'm pretty sure it's around 41 though as that seems to be the most common of the reports.<br>
<br>
The pelts appear to only drop off the Snow Cougars and Tundra Kodiaks that roam the Eastern Wastes.  Don't waste time in Iceclad or Great Divide looking for these.  The HQ Cougar skins are reasonably common, but the Kodiak Pelts are annoyingly rare.  If you're lucky, you may find a HQ Kodiak pelt on 1/10 of your kills, if you're unlucky it may be more like 1/50.  Once you have combined the pelts, the resulting blanket is NO DROP.  Turn in the blanket to Garadain and you will get your first ring.<br>
<br>
Note: at level 35 you may have a tough time soloing the cougars and kodiaks, best to have a partner at this point.<br>
<br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP  <br>
AC: +1 Str: +1 Magic Resist: +1  <br>
Weight: 0.1 <br>
Classes: All Classes  <br>
Races: All Races  <br>
Inventory Slot: Finger<br> <br>

